<div class="c220_22">
<div id="v220.22.1"><span class="H464 s">Then Eliphaz</span><span class="H8489 s"> the Temanite</span><span class="H6030 s"> answered</span><span class="H559 s"> and said</span>,</div>
<div id="v220.22.2"><span class="H1397 s">Can a man</span><span class="H5532 s"> be profitable</span><span class="H410 s"> unto God</span><span class="H3588 s">, as</span><span class="H7919 s"> he that is wise</span><span class="H5532 s"> may be profitable</span> unto himself? <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (as he…: or, if he may be profitable, doth his good success depend thereon?)</span></div>
<div id="v220.22.3"><span class="H2656 s"><i>Is it</i> any pleasure</span><span class="H7706 s"> to the Almighty</span><span class="H6663 s">, that thou art righteous</span><span class="H1215 s">? or <i>is it</i> gain</span><span class="H1870 s"> <i>to him</i>, that thou makest thy ways</span><span class="H8552 s"> perfect</span>?</div>
<div id="v220.22.4"><span class="H3198 s">Will he reprove</span><span class="H3374 s"> thee for fear</span><span class="H935 s"> of thee? will he enter</span><span class="H4941 s"> with thee into judgment</span>?</div>
<div id="v220.22.5"><span class="H7451 s"><i>Is</i> not thy wickedness</span><span class="H7227 s"> great</span><span class="H5771 s">? and thine iniquities</span><span class="H7093 s"> infinite</span>?</div>
<div id="v220.22.6"><span class="H2254 s">For thou hast taken a pledge</span><span class="H251 s"> from thy brother</span><span class="H2600 s"> for nought</span><span class="H6584 s">, and stripped</span><span class="H6174 s"> the naked</span><span class="H899 s"> of their clothing</span>. <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (the naked…: Heb. the clothes of the naked)</span></div>
<div id="v220.22.7"><span class="H4325 s">Thou hast not given water</span><span class="H5889 s"> to the weary</span><span class="H8248 s"> to drink</span><span class="H4513 s">, and thou hast withholden</span><span class="H3899 s"> bread</span><span class="H7457 s"> from the hungry</span>.</div>
<div id="v220.22.8"><span class="H2220 s">But <i>as for</i> the mighty</span><span class="H376 s"> man</span><span class="H776 s">, he had the earth</span><span class="H5375 s">; and the honourable man</span><span class="H6440 s"> †</span><span class="H3427 s"> dwelt</span> in it. <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (mighty…: Heb. man of arm) (honourable…: Heb. eminent, or, accepted for countenance)</span></div>
<div id="v220.22.9"><span class="H7971 s">Thou hast sent</span><span class="H490 s"> widows</span><span class="H7387 s"> away empty</span><span class="H2220 s">, and the arms</span><span class="H3490 s"> of the fatherless</span><span class="H1792 s"> have been broken</span>.</div>
<div id="v220.22.10"><span class="H6341 s">Therefore snares</span><span class="H5439 s"> <i>are</i> round about</span><span class="H6597 s"> thee, and sudden</span><span class="H6343 s"> fear</span><span class="H926 s"> troubleth</span> thee;</div>
<div id="v220.22.11"><span class="H2822 s">Or darkness</span><span class="H7200 s">, <i>that</i> thou canst not see</span><span class="H8229 s">; and abundance</span><span class="H4325 s"> of waters</span><span class="H3680 s"> cover</span> thee.</div>
<div id="v220.22.12"><span class="H433 s"><i>Is</i> not God</span><span class="H1363 s"> in the height</span><span class="H8064 s"> of heaven</span><span class="H7200 s">? and behold</span><span class="H7218 s"> the height</span><span class="H3556 s"> of the stars</span><span class="H7311 s">, how high</span> they are! <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (height of the stars: Heb. head of the stars)</span></div>
<div id="v220.22.13"><span class="H559 s">And thou sayest</span><span class="H410 s">, How doth God</span><span class="H3045 s"> know</span><span class="H8199 s">? can he judge</span><span class="H6205 s"> through the dark cloud</span>? <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (How: or, What)</span></div>
<div id="v220.22.14"><span class="H5645 s">Thick clouds</span><span class="H5643 s"> <i>are</i> a covering</span><span class="H7200 s"> to him, that he seeth</span><span class="H1980 s"> not; and he walketh</span><span class="H2329 s"> in the circuit</span><span class="H8064 s"> of heaven</span>.</div>
<div id="v220.22.15"><span class="H8104 s">Hast thou marked</span><span class="H5769 s"> the old</span><span class="H734 s"> way</span><span class="H205 s"> which wicked</span><span class="H4962 s"> men</span><span class="H1869 s"> have trodden</span>?</div>
<div id="v220.22.16"><span class="H7059 s">Which were cut down</span><span class="H6256 s"> out of time</span><span class="H3247 s">, whose foundation</span><span class="H3332 s"> was overflown</span><span class="H5104 s"> with a flood</span>: <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (whose…: Heb. a flood was poured upon their foundation)</span></div>
<div id="v220.22.17"><span class="H559 s">Which said</span><span class="H410 s"> unto God</span><span class="H5493 s">, Depart</span><span class="H7706 s"> from us: and what can the Almighty</span><span class="H6466 s"> do</span> for them? <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (for: or, to)</span></div>
<div id="v220.22.18"><span class="H4390 s">Yet he filled</span><span class="H1004 s"> their houses</span><span class="H2896 s"> with good</span><span class="H6098 s"> <i>things</i>: but the counsel</span><span class="H7563 s"> of the wicked</span><span class="H7368 s"> is far</span> from me.</div>
<div id="v220.22.19"><span class="H6662 s">The righteous</span><span class="H7200 s"> see</span><span class="H8055 s"> <i>it</i>, and are glad</span><span class="H5355 s">: and the innocent</span><span class="H3932 s"> laugh them to scorn</span>.</div>
<div id="v220.22.20"><span class="H518 s">Whereas</span><span class="H7009 s"> our substance</span><span class="H3582 s"> is not cut down</span><span class="H3499 s">, but the remnant</span><span class="H784 s"> of them the fire</span><span class="H398 s"> consumeth</span>. <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (substance: or, estate) (the remnant…: or, their excellency)</span></div>
<div id="v220.22.21"><span class="H5532 s">Acquaint</span><span class="H7999 s"> now thyself with him, and be at peace</span><span class="H2896 s">: thereby good</span><span class="H935 s"> shall come</span> unto thee. <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (him: that is, God)</span></div>
<div id="v220.22.22"><span class="H3947 s">Receive</span><span class="H8451 s">, I pray thee, the law</span><span class="H6310 s"> from his mouth</span><span class="H7760 s">, and lay up</span><span class="H561 s"> his words</span><span class="H3824 s"> in thine heart</span>.</div>
<div id="v220.22.23"><span class="H7725 s">If thou return</span><span class="H7706 s"> to the Almighty</span><span class="H1129 s">, thou shalt be built up</span><span class="H7368 s">, thou shalt put away</span><span class="H5766 s"> iniquity</span><span class="H7368 s"> far</span><span class="H168 s"> from thy tabernacles</span>.</div>
<div id="v220.22.24"><span class="H7896 s">Then shalt thou lay up</span><span class="H1220 s"> gold</span><span class="H5921 s"> as</span><span class="H6083 s"> dust</span><span class="H211 s">, and the <i>gold</i> of Ophir</span><span class="H6697 s"> as the stones</span><span class="H5158 s"> of the brooks</span>. <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (as dust: or, on the dust)</span></div>
<div id="v220.22.25"><span class="H7706 s">Yea, the Almighty</span><span class="H1220 s"> shall be thy defence</span><span class="H8443 s">, and thou shalt have plenty</span><span class="H3701 s"> of silver</span>. <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (defence: or, gold) (plenty…: Heb. silver of strength)</span></div>
<div id="v220.22.26"><span class="H6026 s">For then shalt thou have thy delight</span><span class="H7706 s"> in the Almighty</span><span class="H5375 s">, and shalt lift up</span><span class="H6440 s"> thy face</span><span class="H433 s"> unto God</span>.</div>
<div id="v220.22.27"><span class="H6279 s">Thou shalt make thy prayer</span><span class="H8085 s"> unto him, and he shall hear</span><span class="H7999 s"> thee, and thou shalt pay</span><span class="H5088 s"> thy vows</span>.</div>
<div id="v220.22.28"><span class="H1504 s">Thou shalt also decree</span><span class="H562 s"> a thing</span><span class="H6965 s">, and it shall be established</span><span class="H216 s"> unto thee: and the light</span><span class="H5050 s"> shall shine</span><span class="H1870 s"> upon thy ways</span>.</div>
<div id="v220.22.29"><span class="H8213 s">When <i>men</i> are cast down</span><span class="H559 s">, then thou shalt say</span><span class="H1466 s">, <i>There is</i> lifting up</span><span class="H3467 s">; and he shall save</span><span class="H7807 s"> the humble</span><span class="H5869 s"> person</span>. <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (the humble…: Heb. him that hath low eyes)</span></div>
<div id="v220.22.30"><span class="H4422 s">He shall deliver</span><span class="H336 s"> the island</span><span class="H5355 s"> of the innocent</span><span class="H4422 s">: and it is delivered</span><span class="H1252 s"> by the pureness</span><span class="H3709 s"> of thine hands</span>. <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (He shall…: or, The innocent shall deliver the island)</span></div></div>
